title: Coronavirus update: Global death toll passes 100,000, as recovered South Korean patients test positive again
description: The global death toll hits 100,000 as 1.6 million people battle the virus, Boris Johnson is up and walking and in "extremely good spirits", but in South Korea, recovered patients are testing positive in what appears to be a second round of COVID-19.
content:
Posted 
April 11, 2020 06:33:11
A grim milestone has been hit as the global death toll of COVID-19 passes 100,000, but in South Korea, recovered patients are testing positive in what appears to be a second round of the new coronavirus.
